ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 20th day of June, 2005, this court accepts jurisdiction over this matter under the collateral order doctrine. Commonwealth v. Dennis, 580 Pa. 95, 859 A.2d 1270 (2004). Further, the order of the Court of Common Pleas of Lancaster County is VACATED. Commonwealth v. Williams, 557 Pa. 207, 732 A.2d 1167 (1999). Jurisdiction relinquished.
Justice EAKIN did not participate in this matter.
Justice NIGRO dissents.
